cs.OS, cs.EM, cs.RT, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper discusses real-time scheduling for safety-critical systems, which involves operating systems (cs.OS), embedded systems (cs.EM), and real-time systems (cs.RT). The focus on certification requirements and varying levels of criticality suggests a systems (cs.SY) perspective. Finally, the proposed algorithm and schedulability test involve programming languages (cs.PL).
